The paper discusses the use of belief propagation and its variants for approximate inference, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on dynamic update schedules and their impact on running time and convergence suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), while the use of upper bounds and message errors suggests a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
